=E2=80=99t going to persuade ossified voters in Birmingham or Brooklyn, whe=
re they already hold religious
opinions about the guy. But in a margin-of-error election that will be deci=
ded by not just a handful of states, but a half-dozen <i>districts</i> in v=
arious metro areas, like Detroit, an unambiguous and incontrovertible rulin=
